ENTRY       EC 3.6.3.7                  Enzyme
NAME        Na+-exporting ATPase
CLASS       Hydrolases;
            Acting on acid anhydrides;
            Acting on acid anhydrides to catalyse transmembrane movement of substances
SYSNAME     ATP phosphohydrolase (Na+-exporting)
REACTION    ATP + H2O + Na+in = ADP + phosphate + Na+out [RN:R00086]
ALL_REAC    R00086
SUBSTRATE   ATP [CPD:C00002];
            H2O [CPD:C00001];
            Na+ [CPD:C01330]
PRODUCT     ADP [CPD:C00008];
            phosphate [CPD:C00009];
            Na+ [CPD:C01330]
COMMENT     A P-type ATPase that undergoes covalent phosphorylation during the transport cycle. This enzyme from yeast is involved in the efflux of Na+, with one ion being exported per ATP hydrolysed.
